    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-14T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-14T05:00:00-05:00" n="201"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7043: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-14T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 14, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 14—1:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>276. Legation’s 274, June 14, noon. Following from American Consul General at
                    Mukden.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“June 14, 3 p.m. My June 13, noon. Local press today published obviously
                        inspired reports alleging that Chiang Kai-shek is supplying arms to Chahar
                        chairman and urging him to continue anti-Japanese activities and to maintain
                        contact with Outer Mongolia and Soviet Russia. Reports add that former
                        northern clique leaders are urging Chiang to endeavor embroil Japan lobby
                            [<hi rend="italic">military?</hi>] with powers having North China
                        interests.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
